---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Le Jardin — Moulin à Rêves" description="Le Jardin: the garden cottage at Moulin à Rêves. 3 bedrooms, sleeps 6, wrapped in wisteria with a terrace made for long afternoons.">

  <Fragment slot="schema">
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "VacationRental",
      "name": "Le Jardin — Moulin à Rêves",
      "description": "The garden cottage at Moulin à Rêves. 3 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms, sleeps 6. Wrapped in wisteria with a south-facing terrace made for long afternoons.",
      "url": "https://moulin-a-reves.com/homes/le-jardin/",
      "image": "/images/homes/le-jardin-hero.webp",
      "numberOfBedrooms": 3,
      "numberOfBathroomsTotal": 2,
      "occupancy": { "@type": "QuantitativeValue", "value": 6 },
      "floorSize": { "@type": "QuantitativeValue", "value": 130, "unitCode": "MTK" },
      "petsAllowed": true,
      "address": {
        "@type": "PostalAddress",
        "addressLocality": "Barbizon",
        "addressRegion": "Seine-et-Marne",
        "addressCountry": "FR"
      },
      "geo": {
        "@type": "GeoCoordinates",
        "latitude": 48.4433,
        "longitude": 2.6033
      },
      "amenityFeature": [
        {"@type": "LocationFeatureSpecification", "name": "WiFi", "value": true},
        {"@type": "LocationFeatureSpecification", "name": "Kitchen", "value": true},
        {"@type": "LocationFeatureSpecification", "name": "Wood-burning Stove", "value": true},
        {"@type": "LocationFeatureSpecification", "name": "Garden", "value": true},
        {"@type": "LocationFeatureSpecification", "name": "Hot Tub", "value": true}
      ]
    })} />
  </Fragment>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero__image">
      <img src="/images/homes/le-jardin-hero.webp" alt="Le Jardin — garden cottage wrapped in wisteria with a private terrace" />
    </div>
    <div class="hero__overlay"></div>
    <div class="hero__content">
      <h1 class="hero__title">Le Jardin</h1>
      <p class="hero__tagline" data-i18n="jardin.hero.tagline">The garden cottage. Wisteria, quiet, and afternoons that stretch.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Stats Bar -->
  <section class="section" style="padding-top: 48px; padding-bottom: 48px;">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="stats-bar">
        <div class="stats-bar__item">
          <div class="stats-bar__number">3</div>
          <div class="stats-bar__label" data-i18n="jardin.stats.bedrooms">Bedrooms</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stats-bar__item">
          <div class="stats-bar__number">2</div>
          <div class="stats-bar__label" data-i18n="jardin.stats.bathrooms">Bathrooms</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stats-bar__item">
          <div class="stats-bar__number">6</div>
          <div class="stats-bar__label" data-i18n="jardin.stats.guests">Guests</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stats-bar__item">
          <div class="stats-bar__number">130</div>
          <div class="stats-bar__label">m&sup2;</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Narrative Description -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container--narrow fade-in">
      <h2 data-i18n="jardin.narrative.heading">The Quiet One</h2>
      <div style="margin-top: 32px;">
        <p data-i18n="jardin.narrative.p1">
          You'll find Le Jardin at the far end of the compound, past the shared garden and the old stone wall where the roses climb. It's the smallest of the three houses and, by a comfortable margin, the quietest. The wisteria that covers the south-facing wall blooms in late spring — heavy, fragrant clusters of pale violet that the bees work through all morning — and even after the flowers have dropped, the twisted vine throws a dappled shade across the terrace that's worth the visit on its own.
        </p>
        <p data-i18n="jardin.narrative.p2" style="margin-top: 20px;">
          The terrace is where you'll spend most of your time. It faces south and west, catching sun from mid-morning through sunset, and it's large enough for a table, a pair of lounge chairs, and the kind of scattered toys that accumulate when children have been playing outdoors all afternoon. You'll eat dinner here most evenings — the warmth holds in the stone long after the air has cooled — and on clear nights, away from any city light, the sky above the garden is thick with stars.
        </p>
        <p data-i18n="jardin.narrative.p3" style="margin-top: 20px;">
          Inside, Le Jardin has the feel of a place that knows what it is. The rooms are not large, but they're well-proportioned and full of light. The kitchen is galley-style, practical and pretty, with a window above the sink that looks directly into the garden. You'll cook with the window open in summer, the scent of thyme drifting in from the border just outside. The living room has a wood-burning stove, two deep armchairs, and a wall of books — mostly French, a shelf of English, and a basket of picture books for children who have been running all day and are finally ready to sit still.
        </p>
        <p data-i18n="jardin.narrative.p4" style="margin-top: 20px;">
          The bedrooms are upstairs, tucked beneath a roofline of old terra cotta tiles. The master looks south over the garden and beyond to the treeline of Fontainebleau Forest. You'll fall asleep to silence here — real silence, the kind where you can hear your own breathing — and wake to birdsong that starts tentatively, then builds into the full chorus of a French country morning.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Room by Room -->
  <section class="section section--stone">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="text-center fade-in" style="margin-bottom: 64px;">
        <h2 data-i18n="jardin.rooms.heading">Room by Room</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="grid grid--3">
        <div class="card fade-in">
          <div class="card__image">
            <img src="/images/bridge-garden.webp" alt="Le Jardin master bedroom with south-facing garden views at Moulin à Rêves, Barbizon" />
          </div>
          <div class="card__body">
            <h3 class="card__title" data-i18n="jardin.room.master.title">Master Bedroom</h3>
            <p class="card__description" data-i18n="jardin.room.master.desc">King bed facing south, with views over the garden to the forest. En-suite shower room with hand-made tiles and warm limestone floor.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card fade-in">
          <div class="card__image">
            <img src="/images/bridge-garden.webp" alt="Le Jardin rose room with queen bed beneath sloping roofline at Moulin à Rêves" />
          </div>
          <div class="card__body">
            <h3 class="card__title" data-i18n="jardin.room.rose.title">The Rose Room</h3>
            <p class="card__description" data-i18n="jardin.room.rose.desc">Queen bed beneath the sloping roofline. The window frames the climbing rose on the garden wall. A quiet, simple, beautiful room.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card fade-in">
          <div class="card__image">
            <img src="/images/bridge-garden.webp" alt="Le Jardin treetop room with twin beds and dormer window at Moulin à Rêves" />
          </div>
          <div class="card__body">
            <h3 class="card__title" data-i18n="jardin.room.treetop.title">The Treetop Room</h3>
            <p class="card__description" data-i18n="jardin.room.treetop.desc">Two single beds at the highest point of the house, with a dormer window that looks into the branches of the walnut tree. Children's favourite.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card fade-in">
          <div class="card__image">
            <img src="/images/bridge-garden.webp" alt="Le Jardin galley kitchen with garden-facing window at Moulin à Rêves, Barbizon" />
          </div>
          <div class="card__body">
            <h3 class="card__title" data-i18n="jardin.room.kitchen.title">Kitchen</h3>
            <p class="card__description" data-i18n="jardin.room.kitchen.desc">Galley kitchen with garden-facing window. Four-burner hob, oven, dishwasher, and everything you need to cook with what you found at the marche.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card fade-in">
          <div class="card__image">
            <img src="/images/screening-room.webp" alt="Le Jardin living room with wood-burning stove and bookshelves at Moulin à Rêves" />
          </div>
          <div class="card__body">
            <h3 class="card__title" data-i18n="jardin.room.living.title">Living Room</h3>
            <p class="card__description" data-i18n="jardin.room.living.desc">Wood-burning stove, two deep armchairs, a wall of books. Doors open onto the terrace. The room where rainy afternoons become a gift.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card fade-in">
          <div class="card__image">
            <img src="/images/gazebo-dining.webp" alt="Le Jardin south-facing wisteria-shaded terrace with garden views at Moulin à Rêves" />
          </div>
          <div class="card__body">
            <h3 class="card__title" data-i18n="jardin.room.terrace.title">The Terrace</h3>
            <p class="card__description" data-i18n="jardin.room.terrace.desc">South-facing stone terrace beneath the wisteria. Table for six, lounge chairs, and an uninterrupted view of the garden and forest beyond.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Amenities -->
